caption: I liked the burgers here. Must try for all vegans.

One of my favorite places in Urbana. Nice selection of vegan items. Favorites include the vicken “chicken” sandwich and the Ruben on marbled rye with horseradish and melty mozz. The ketchup is house-made and is probably the best I’ve ever had. The juices and house-made desserts are also stellar. Have to agree with the other reviewer about the service. It can be somewhat spotty and cold or abrupt.
I was able to email with the head chef about an order and they were amazing! Quick responses and followed up with me about the order as well. I am very pleased!
As a loyal customer, I always ordered food twice a week. The only thing i dislike is the lady should treat customers a lil bit nicer, specially on the phone.

I had the impossible burger with side of fries, my wife had the Philly Cheezesteak sandwich. We also got a drink called "Medusa's Curse". Everything was great and you could tell the food was handmade even down to the ketchup! I would highly recommend going here and trying out their food :)
Just had the seitan bahn mi - so great!  Thanks, DD!
I have been skeptical about trying eggplant 🍆 but, Olympia recommended it... I tried it at the Dancing Dog and LOVED IT! Tamara@globalsolutionshrc.com
The vicken is the best thing on the menu period.
Tim yum yum yum yuuuum! Perfect vegan pesto grilled "cheese." Perfectly healthy & energizing juice. As dancing dog, though,  they should have a healthy dog treat for the pups!

My friend and I came in for lunch one afternoon and I am so glad that we did! I was very excited to try an all-vegan menu. I enjoyed their broccoli soup, a fresh glass of orange juice, and the dancing dog nachos. Everything was great from service to taste. My orange juice and soup were exceptional!  The ambiance that afternoon was very calm and perfect for the two of us. I love the decor and the wait staff is very kind! I finished my meal with a freshly baked chocolate chip cookie - which was easily one of the best cookies I've ever had. Definitely recommend!
please try their chocolate cake!
Love the vegan meals and their chocolate cake really is to die for!

Excellent vegan place. My favorite here is garlic vicked patty with fieasta and served with fries. The burger and the fries here are probably the best in town.  In terms of starters, nachos is really good. Desert, don't forget to try death by chocolate. It is AMAZING!  I wish they were open in the evening until 9pm.

Went for Sunday brunch on my first visit, and will definitely be back! From what I overheard when staff were talking to each other, it was exceptionally busy, even for a Sunday. We put our names in for a table and they called my phone sooner than expected to tell me it was ready, so it's a good thing I'd not gone far up the street! As a result of the crowd, items were a bit slow to come out, but without visiting again at different times I can't say whether that was unusual.  As for the food, vegans don't often have an abundance of choice on most menus; this was my first time at an all-vegan restaurant, so I was delighted and almost overwhelmed with options! I had a couple mimosas (tasted very refreshing, and was so cute with the pink-oramge gradient I wish I'd remembered to take a picture) and waffles with banana and walnuts on top. It came with "butter," strawberry compote, and maple syrup in little cups. My partner got the breakfast pizza, and based on that we definitely want to come on a Saturday night to try their deep dish!  This was worth traveling from the Bloomington-Normal area for, and I'll definitely return, but not with anybody in a hurry.

Awesome artwork, great staff who are always pleasant and jamming great tunes in the back, warm friendly environment. I only get smoothies from here, as I am not a vegan, but food always smells great and is much appreciated by our customers at GREED HUB. I had the pineapple blueberry love smoothies, but banana was far too overbearing on the taste, as could not even taste the pineapple, nor even the ginger or much of blueberry, but it was not bad, just need to request no banana next time, see if it is much better tasting for me, as I am not much a fan of banana, but needed the potassium today. Straw was weak, broke and made it difficult to drink from too, but will soon be using bamboo ones for environment.  I do love this place, and bet you will too. I met people who became friends here, and bought owner a bendable dog I felt they needed, and was thanked often for it. Really love dogs, lot of dog friendly art, and even sell vegan dog biscuits. If you REALLY LOVE THIS PLACE, THEY SELL T SHIRTS AND STICKERS, SO SHOW YOUR APPRECIATION OTHERS CAN ENJOY OR LEARN ABOUT. SHIRTS HAVE BRILLIANTLY BEAUTIFUL COLORS!
Everything is always wonderful! Vegan dream, and non vegans get ready to fall in love with vegan food.
awful hospitality. the waitress looks really not in the mood. also do not try to take my plate when im obviously not done with it.

You need to come here in no hurry to order or receive food, the service is slow, but the food is delicious. I highly recommend getting the Mazze Plate, the cashew chevre cheeze is amazing! The Crispy v-chik'n patty  is from far my favorite thing on the menu! The house-made ketchup is also delicious. Also, try the cakes and fresh juice/smoothie  They are also participating #ccrestaurantweek DINNER—$19  Appetizer—Choose one from our regular menu  Main Course—Choose one our salads, sandwiches or entrées  Dessert—Choose one from our regular menu  Mezze Plate Hummus, kalamata tapenade, cashew chevre cheeze, tomatoes, cucumbers, and sliced, toasted pita bread.  Buffalo Cauliflower Bites Cauliflower florets in a spicy sauce with celery sticks and our house made ranch dressing.  Garlic Vicken Crispy v-chik'n patty with garlic herb aioli, lettuce, tomato, and red onion on a bun. Served with one side and pickles.  Vanilla Lavender Vanilla cake, lavender flowers, vanilla buttercream  Sunshine Banana, Pineapple, Orange,  Lemon, Lemon Zest, & Ginger
Great food.
Nothing organic except for the the tea.
Excellent food, hours restricted for their pizza orders

I wanted to order everything on the menu but decided on the nachos, Gyro, and vanilla lavender cake. They were all awesome! This restaurant is cute, welcoming, and everything is vegan! What more could you ask for? (They even have gluten free options)
Excellent vegan food and great service.
Great food

This is absolutely the place to go if you want a 100% plant-based meal without worrying about accidentally getting something not vegan. There are several fantastic mock-meat options and their house-made vegan mozzarella is easily the best vegan cheese I've ever had. It doesn't have the cheapest menu around, but each item is worth every penny.

A bit expensive but the food is delicious and the deserts are house-made and amazing. Good fresh juices too.  The fact that it's vegan and there are gluten free deserts is a plus, but the important part is that it tastes good. I'm not vegan but I still eat here because of things like the house ketchup and the amaaazing deserts.
Small but tasty
The food is good but only when they have it. Waited 30 minutes to be told that they're out of my order. Then after I selected a substitute, they were out of that too.
Good food at a good price.
Absolutely delicious vegan food! The roasted potatoes and cake are excellent.
Tastes ok but expensive
Vegan's dream restaurant. We loved every one of the four dishes we tried...and the fresh juice too. Great staff and food in the heart of Urbana.
Great food and amazing fresh juices
Quinoa-on-a-bed was just what I was looking for. Great service.
Good food. Good prices. Regular place to frequent.
Tasty, healthy options and a laid back atmosphere.
Fresh made juice and great vegan food.. what more could you need??
Food is great and i love coming here for it but they need to get a new server, the blonde girl isn't very helpful and has a bad attitude.

Visited twice within few months. Kid decided to go to UIUC. And this is one of the 2 vegetarian options in the area (the other one with quite inconvenient open hours). Food is great. I am eager to commit low level crimes to get the Brussels sprouts. Or take a punch in order to get the Buffalo Cauliflower Bites. Liked some of the sauces used in the rest of the items. The smoothies are too heavy for me to go with food but perfectly great otherwise. For sure will be one of the places to stop when we visit in the next 4 years...:-)
Delicious any dessert with chocolate! Also, I have advanced stage stomach cancer. The carrot orange juice made my stomach much more comfortable!
Vega good, service, ok.
So delicious! My "quinoa on a bed" salad was beautiful and the "old hippy blend" tea was yummy and refreshing.
Great food! Great people! Great place for lunch!

The vegan chicken sandwich was good. My only wish is that it could have been dressed with vegan mayo. The type of fries that it came with were not my favorite. My boyfriend said he wished there were more menu items and I agree. The chocolate cake was to die for. The vanilla lavender cake was heavenly. The blue sky sodas they served were unique and tasty. Our server was very nice and pleasant. Definitely will be back!
Great vegan food and dessert

dancing dog is the first vegan restaurant I visited in U-C. It is so lovely! the waitress wear casual clothes like T-shirts, not boring as uniforms, which convinced me that the employee culture of this restaurant is modern. Food are pretty interesting. The dessert(chocolate cake) might be too sweet for me,  so I'd appreciate if the share is not so large. Looking forward to another visit with my mentor next week.
Tasty food with a lovely atmosphere.
I had the buffalo cauliflower tacos and the sunshine smoothie, and both were excellent! Would recommend this place to anyone, vegan or not.
Loved the selection of juice flavors and the hummus!

I'm not vegan and I don't think I've ever been to a vegan restaurant before, so I didn't know what to expect. But I was pleasantly surprised. I tried the impossible burger. I wouldn't say it had me fooled into thinking it was meat by any stretch of the imagination, but it was a very good veggie burger. The fries were very good as well.
Food was good, but service was slow. The restaurant was less than half full, but we had to wait a long time for our food.

They have cauliflower buffalo wings to die for!!! Service is EXCELLENT we had both salads, hummus platter and the Ruben sandwich & a juice - 5 stars!! Oh and two pcs of gluten free cake. Highly recommend.
OMG I cannot say enough about how amazing this restaurant is. The ketchup is so tasty oh, so is the garlic aioli, The V chicken changed my life. I will go back again and again
Service was great. Plenty of variety of plates to choose from. Unfortunately I did not have room for dessert otherwise I for sure would have tried one of their cakes. I'll be back!!
Great vegetarian food.
The lavender cake is wonderful! Very fast service as well! Nice spot to try out!
Vegan and yummy?  Yes, please.
Quick service, delicious brownie.
Super great atmoshere and food.  I had the special of the day and will be going back for more to try
The Reuben tasted like the real thing
Excellent food, although a bit pricey. They had nailed the pesto chikn sandwich and the lentil soup.  I'd definitely be back!

I can not say enough how much I love this place! It is a good thing I live in Chicago or I would be here ALL the time. I was in town for work a few weeks and ordered from here at least once a week the entire time.  My favorite is the crispy chicken sandwich with the garlic mayo. YUM. I physically had a hard time ordering anything else, but when I did order something else it was good. The soups of the day were always the bomb. They do have the impossible burger but it is kinda hard to tell because it isn't on the menu but you can just ask for it.  The service has been good every time also. One time I had to wait awhile for a pickup order but it was no big deal and the cashier was very courteous. Service in restaurant was also nice and quick. Thank you for being a great representation of how amazing a vegan place can be!
Fantastic burger & fries, but their housemade tomato sauce is a real stand out!

Great vegan place! I'm not vegan but will happily eat there anytime with folks who don't eat meat or dairy. It's a relaxed atmosphere, and the food is amazing! They also have some of the BEST desserts, vegan or otherwise, in town. Death by Chocolate Cake and Oatmeal Cream Pie Cookies are my favs.
Great vegan entrees!
The food wait is a bit long
Great vegan restaurant
Coffee and cream was delicious. I had the Vicken and it was TASTY! Ketchup wasn’t my fav but the fries were really good.
I love the food here. This is my vegan stop when I’m working anywhere close. Love it here. Get the special, whatever it my be.
Amazing food, clean atmosphere, and pleasant staff. A great dining experience and a a place i would be very happy to bring non-vegan friends and family!
First time there for Sunday brunch! So much flavor!
I stop here every single time I am in Urbana. The food is so good. I've tried almost everything on the menu. Staff are super friendly and fast

This is my favorite restaurant literally ever. All of their food is consistently above par and I don’t have to worry about if it is complementary to my diet choices. Honestly I would rather spend my college tuition here than getting an education.
Brilliant food, great variety of beverages (fresh juices, teas and coffees) to choose from, what's not to like? Absolutely love this place!

It was ok, we ordered several things off the menu and weren't really impressed. My sandwich tasted like a school chicken patty and all I tasted in my blueberry cobbler smoothie was bananas, the cake was tough and chewy and way to sweet. The only thing that was really good was the buffalo cauliflower bites, but you only get about 8 small pieces for almost $8. We spent over $30 for two people and walked out still hungry. And if that wasn't enough for me to never go back the person who took our order was very short and rude. Im sorry but I wouldn't reccrreco
I highly recommend "The Tingler" fresh juice!
Love this vegan eatery.  Great food, great service, great prices.  Loved all of it.
Best vegan restaurant in CU!
Really slow service. Took us 1.5 hours to get a stirfry and two grilled cheese sandwiches.
Loved the options!
Thank you Dancing Dog for a wonderful lunch. I had the nachos and loved them. Look forward to seeing you again soon.

Went to order a vegan pizza was informed that they couldn't cook it until 5 so went back and they informed me it would be 45 minutes. Went back and then informed me it would be another 10 minutes. I was seriously unimpressed.

Great vegan spot in Urbana. Went on a Sunday when they opened and was a little disappointed that there was only a brunch menu at the time, but the food was still impressive. Portions are on the smaller side, but it was just enough so I wasn't too full or still hungry.

We went for a weekday lunch. I was in town visiting family and had my dog with me. It was a little hot outside, but they said we could sit on the patio with my dog. The staff was really nice; the patio wasn't set up when we got there, so they brought the table and chairs out for us. We had the Buffalo cauliflower as an appetizer. It was really good. For lunch I had a grilled cheese and tomato soup. It was delicious. I approve.
Always good food!
Absolutely amazing! Best food ever!
Best vegan restaurant in the area! The food, service and desserts are top notch!
Went there for the Sunday brunch, the food was great :) good service too
Always great service and food.
Great little place to have in Urbana!  100% vegan.  The Impossible Burger and deep dish pizza (Saturday nights only) are stars on the menu.
Food so good it's not right to call it an 'imitation'.
A vegan spot, that always hits the spot! Good food and atmosphere!
Fantastic service and the food was delicious.  I can't wait to go back for more nachos!
A unique place to eat.  Very good food.

This is a fantastic vegan restaurant. They provide one of the best deep dish pizzas in Chambana. Even non vegans would agree. Their cupcakes and desserts are delicious and are a must try. Regardless, definitely try the deep dish pizza. The vegan sausage is delicious, though the best part is the vegan mozerrella. IT is fabulous. Go get any deep dish n be wowed by it and finish it off with amazing desserts.  As for the ambience, it is beautiful, they have seating upstairs that has some books and is generally a nice cafe. It is not that big so it feels claustrophobic if it gets crowded.
Very impressed for a vegan place. I had the Rueben which was tasty. I'll go back anytime I'm trying to accommodate someone's diet.
Amazing as always!!

The food is very good, but almost too good.  For instance, the vegan fish filet tasted and had the texture of fish.  I could not eat it because it was so life-like. I wish they had options that were not meat 'look alikes'.  However, they have a business to run and know what sells.  The food is very good,  service staff are pleasant, and it seems clean.
Great Vegan Restaurant and excellent service.
Excellent Vegan Food.  Great "burger" and fries.
They are good. Just good in my humble opinion.
Very good, tasty and filling vegan burger
My son Vego loved his sauerkraut!! So fresh. We looked for the dancing dog, but the polite server informed us it was only a name :/
So good that I cant tell if I'm eating vegan or not

If you love food, you'll love Dancing Dog. Yeah, it's a vegan place, so what? That just means that all of their delicious food is 100% guilt free. The staff are always cheery, they have good specials (especially the desserts), and the menu is so big! They also have a great brunch selection, and amazing deep dish pizza on Saturday evenings. They're definitely earned the awesome reputation!
Really good vegan food.  Great smoothies.  Excellent cookies.  Nice, casual, friendly environment for eating.
Went here for Brunch and had the Vicken Sandwich. Loved it!
Even though they have reduced their menu, it's still one of our favorite places to eat because vegan is hard to find. Their Saturday night, deep dish pizza is superb.
Excellent vegan food, well prepared. Service is prompt and friendly. The menu options are good but could be enhanced with a few more choices.
Excellent vegan place!

Their vegan deep dish pizza is actually really good! I did not have high expectations since it's diary free, but I was pleasantly surprised. The cashew chèvre & almond mozzarella cheeses have a unique flavor/texture that goes well with the rest of the pizza. You can only order it after 5pm on Saturday and from my experience, you only have about 90-120 minutes before it's sold out. I would highly recommend you try it out if you have the chance. I'm unable to comment on the dine in service since I have always ordered my food to go, but the staff seemed friendly for the short periods that I was there.
I love going there.. great food great people
Excellent classic vegan burger and wonderful tea!!!! The atmosphere is trendy but relaxing! I cannot wait to go back!!!

Really expensive for what you get. Overheard the staff saying they serve gardein brand foods, which probably contributes to the high price and lack of quality, since you can buy those frozen across the street. Would love it if they would make more of their foods in house. As a long time vegan I can attest it's not a good representation of vegan food.

Went out our way to visit The Dancing Dog and it was amazing! First of all, my kids are very picky and they were accommodating to the extreme. At one point they overheard my daughter crying about her smoothie being to lemony and they replaced it with a another smoothie, no lemon, and without prompting.  My mom was hesitant going to an all-vegan place but liked her tacos and dessert. The tacos were amazing, and we also tried the Ruben and Pesto Grilled Cheeze and they were all awesome. For us, the Pesto Grilled Cheeze was the clear winner and the desserts (especially oatmeal cream pie) and coffee were a treat.  Also a comfy little lounge is upstairs to recline and enjoy the space.

As it is all vegan, all the time, the Reuben is my favorite. But today (July 27, 2017) I had a burger, and it was really good! But the highlight of this evening was a unique cake call, 'Memphis Mafia'... This is now officially my favorite cake!.. Yum yum

Great service, great food. Shared the delicious brussel sprout appetizer and had a veggie burger for lunch. Service was lightening quick and the food was amazing. Creative menu with everything fresh and home made. Highly recommend!
Simply Amazing!!
Excellent food. Attentive service.
Kosher and Vegan
Yummy nachos! Fiesta burger was so good

My hubby & I are no longer exclusive vegans, however, while traveling, it's tuff to find restaurants serving Paleo -clean foods. So we tried the Dancing Dog. Friendly, informed staff, clean facility,  and ... WONDERFULLY tasting food choices. Will definitely return here when in the area.
Healthy and delicious vegan meal.
The best vegetarian food I have had in US in over a year! Loved the Garlic Vicken and the Vegetable Stir-fry, I will definitely be going back for more. Not a fan of the smoothies though.
The nachos had fresh ingredients. The staff was acceptable.
Great healthy food fast. Breakfast burrito and fruit veggie juice. All homemade.

We've been coming to Dancing Dog since they opened. They've definitely gotten better over time. Brunch, lunch, and dinner are all so tasty. The deep dish pizza is a very special Saturday treat, for lovers and friends, for vegans as well as omnis. The desserts are rich and sweet. The music tends to be varied but good (classic Neil Young to the White Stripes), and I love the local/student art on the walls. The servers tend to be friendly and helpful too. No complaints.

The service was incredibly slow. And that's saying something because I'm a super patience person. It was on the evening of First Friday. They were running a smaller menu than usual, and they were out of a ton of stuff on the smaller menu. We ordered nachos with the vegan sausage, but they came out without, and then proceeded to  tell us they were out of it. I'm giving it three stars because they gave us a free dessert for our troubles. I'm really hoping that next time I go things will be better.
Love this restaurant! Their DD Burger is fantastic!

So, in an effort to start eating more fruits and veggies, and fewer dairy and meat products, I tried Dancing Dog Eatery, a vegan restaurant, today. I had the pesto grilled cheese sandwich and it was really beyond my expectations of what a grilled cheese sandwich would taste like that has a 'fake' cheese made out of cashews. Really incredible. It was delicious. I really like pesto, and this, too, has been created without Parmesan, but without compromising flavor. I also tried the Tomato Bisque soup, which was the soup of the day, and it was super tasty. I also ordered the Memphis Mafia cake, and frankly, can't say enough about that. Its bananas, literally. I highly recommend, and I'll be back to sample their dishes one by one. Of course, it's more expensive than a typical lunch I'd purchase, but with the difficulty of cooking vegan, I'd say well worth the extra dough.
Food is just okay. Prices are rather high.
Great idea, but disappointing flavor. Extremely limited selection.
Love this place! Great vegan food. Even my omnivore friends love the food.

I am not a Vegan by any means, I like my meats and cheeses, but my sister has recently become Vegan so I suggested we go there for her birthday. Of course suggestions aren’t always set in stone and as the day closed in I became more hesitant about going. I finally caved…it’s only one meal right? I can suck it up. Needless to say, I was slightly shocked and pleasantly surprised with the quality and flavor of the food. I guess I set myself up psychologically, thinking it has to be disgusting, but it was far from gross. I ordered the deep dish pizza and it was amazing! I was a little leery about the wheat sausage, but I ordered it anyway. It has a nice kick to it. This will now be a go to place for my sister when she comes into town.
Great service, great food and they actually make vegan food, not just heated up preprocessed garbage like so many other places.
Love the food and atmosphere.
Vegan tacos really are good!

Excellent! Went in today and had a Reuben!! Friendly service and excellent menu! I moved from Michigan (go blue!) and miss all the vegan restaurants back home. I am so very pleased I found The Dancing Dog! It is a joy to eat at a place where I do not have to ask a million questions about ingredients or order off 'sides' menus or always have a salad! The chocolate cake I had for dessert was soooo good! Portions are large and prices are reasonable. Although I did not try a juice many customers came in for just that while I was eating.💚 Place is cozy. If anything, you MUST drop in for a dessert!! 😁😁
Good vegan food
Delicious vegan food!
Amazing and surprisingly excellent.  Great selection.  Warm and friendly service.

Came here for the deep dish pizza, which is only served during Saturday evening, and was not disappointed! We were told there would be a 45 minute wait, but it actually came out a bit faster. I have tried other items on their menu as well, and they were all good.
Even meat eaters were happy, great fries, desserts awesome. Fresh juice hard to find. Just what doctors  ordered.

The food is quite good. The service is skilled and friendly. The beer, sodas, and deserts are all top quality. The "rural-hip meets old-hippie" atmosphere is charming. The kitchen can be a bit slow when they're busy, but the thing that bugs me is the menu.  To me it's a bit tragic that most of the menu is taken up by vegan imitations of traditional dishes. Vegetables are already good food and don't need to imitate meat or cheese to make good meals; it's impressive that they can make a fish-n-chips with no fish but I'm much more interested in things like the flash fried brussels sprouts (which are delicious).  Now, as an omnivore, maybe I'm not the target audience. After all, I can get a fish-n-chips anywhere, but if you're a vegan with cravings for non-vegan dishes, I imagine Dancing Dog is a godsend for you.  I can't fault them for serving a niche, but I do wonder if they could do so in a way that maintains more appeal for the rest of us.
This place is surprisingly good despite being a meat lover. All their options are delicious and their juices are  the best in town! Totally worth it!!!
Really good place friendly people great service the blueberry muffin was off-the-hook loaded with blueberries and the coffee was great.
Had no idea this was a vegan  restaurant, stayed and enjoyed a rueben. Will be back.

My husband and I moved to the area not too long ago, and I was very excited to learn of a place that served fresh pressed juice. We stopped one Sunday afternoon and ordered 2 juices. The first sips were delicious, but when I went to adjust my straw, I discovered a long hair in my drink! My husband checked his, and there he found a long hair as well. I sent an email to the owner and we received a gift certificate, but I have been very hesitant to return.
Try the pesto grilled cheese.

The interior has very calm vibes, the Cashew Chévre as a starter is absolutely delicious!! The service was a bit slow, but we also went in on a Saturday night at 6. Garlic Vicken Sandwich is fantastic.

I got the 'vegan pulled pork' special some time ago and it was amazing!!! I love their 'nachos' too, and the vegan chicken salads...so impressed with the delicious desserts - so many to choose from :D

Quite possibly the worst Vegan food ever! The black bean burger was bland and unexciting. Their chocolate cake was dry with the consistency of sand. I called in my order for pick up and still waited 45 minutes once I had arrived at the restaurant. Stay away!

As someone who isnt vegan at first i was kinda worried im not into vegan foods but the food here is amazing. It really shows that you can have amazing vegan food. The fibbish tastes even better than real fish its mind blowing.
Amazing vegan food and very helpful servers. Dancing dog has a very creative menu that would be enjoyed by vegans and meat eaters alike. This is a great place to have in downtown Urbana!
Great healthy options
I loved this place. It was wonderful for vegans and vegetarians too. Breakfast, brunch and juice options. Juice was freshly made.
Excellent food. Desserts are wonderful
Good food, friendly service.  Chorizo tacos could use a little more flavor.
Everything I had was delicious, and the staff were delightful!
Although I am not vegan I thought it was very good.  Clean, friendly, quick.  Don't take your meat eater hubby.  He had nachos ..left hungry.

This little cafe is such a comfortable spot to eat. They serve so many of the "comfort foods" but in vegan form. I've been a vegan for 6 years and live in Seattle. This little place in Urbana rivals some of the best vegan places out west. I had the burger, my partner had the fried chicken, my mom had the burrito, and my dad had the fibbish and chips. Let me just tell you. The fibbish and chips is uncanny. You might not even know you're not really eating fish. Vegans can bring their omnivore friends and family here without fear. I hope to visit again the next time I'm in town.
Yummy welcoming place.
Banana French Toast was tasty.
This place is fantastic, it's like that really good restaurant that you'd find in a big city that only locals know about
Food is good, but service is terrible. It is not worth the wait in my opinion. There are only two servers who are running around and it takes forever and they are very unorganized.

Excellent use of space, wonderfully attentive and friendly staff, smallish establishment however doesn't feel cramped it is as though the place is hugging you as you walk in the door. I had tomato soup to go. I enjoyed every second of the smell on the way home. The taste quite literally made me need to sit down. It was rich, tangy, spicy by far the best culinary preparation I have had in some time. In short, phenomenal.

Simply amazing! I eat here every time I drive to Champaign. I love the Reuben and the oatmeal cream pie! I have had the same server every time I've eaten here and she is also very pleasant. I don't know her name but she has curly hair.

The Dancing Dog is the one restaurant in which I've never had a bad meal. They're my go-to place if I want to show my friends how wonderful vegan food can be (without doing the cooking myself). The waitstaff are very patient and friendly. The bathroom, despite being small, is always clean and fresh (they have more than one, but I can only vouch for the women's room). I had a party in their upstairs room a few months ago, and it was a wonderful experience. Unfortunately, I feel obliged to dock a star because though they advertise as being a vegan restaurant, they serve honey. If honey is not something you're concerned about, you won't be disappointed. They also removed my favorite item from the menu (their delicious VLT). They still have it on occasion, but I miss it. Besides that, I recommend the tofu scramble burrito or the fried brussels sprouts. I love this restaurant and hope they open up a new location to spread vegan food across the state.
Good was great but the service was terrible. We didn't receive water or silverware until long after our food was served. We were ignored and waited for over 40 min for our ticket.
Great fresh vegan  food. The choices are varied and the food is awsome.  Highly recommended if you're looking for local awsome healthy vegan food!

I stopped by on my last day in Champaign and am regretting not patronising The Dancing Dog sooner. You can start by creating your own juice or smoothie to carry through your meal. The chilli special had just enough kick to leave you slightly warm and the spaghetti and vballs came with a refreshing candied walnut side-salad. Simple vegan food simply done well.

My husband, mother-in-law, and I enjoyed lunch here today. I'm vegan, my husband's vegetarian, and my mother-in-law just eats whatever. We all enjoyed every bite of our soups, salads, sides, and even French fries with handmade gourmet ketchup! Excellent taste with every bite. And the service and cleanliness of everything was very nice. heart emoticon the artwork on the walls, too! Very cozy with nice low lighting. Very tidy restrooms. The desserts all looked yummy and AWESOME but we are trying to avoid sugar and passed. We will visit again!

So at the sweet corn festival a place of these people food was set up. I've always wanted to try it. First of all the cupcakes that were vanilla and lavender tasted like a candle. Then I tried a bite of the scone and cookie chocolate chip thing. It was like a sponge. I had no saliva until we went to McDonald's and got a coke.

Being a vegan, I have to get creative with what I order from other restaurants. I love that I can come here & pick out anything I want! LOVE the scones & people are always so nice. Even my omni boyfriend loves coming here for the salad topped with quinoa (& he's a picky eater! Lol)
Wonderful atmosphere and the food was delicious too. Cool lounge upstairs. Lots of organic produce. Yummy homemade ketchup.

A very Urbana experience. Their fresh juices are a must here, the menu takes a little more time to decipher and decide. I went with their nachos, which wasn't disappointing. I'll definitely need to take a second visit to truly gauge my thoughts.

Great ambience, it's a quirky restaurant that you can take out or dine in. Awesome juices and vegan dishes. Their soup of the day (veggie chili) was great and their tofu scrambled burrito was out of this world. It was so good we went back twice in 2 days!

Love this place! Stumbled upon it and found fresh and creative smoothies, crunchy veggies, well seasoned soups, baked fries of high quality, friendly service, and a quaint environment. Need I say more?! This place is the real deal and I highly recommended it. I'll be back tomorrow!

Great customer service, laid back background music.  They made a bowl of black beams for us even though it was not on the menu. Nice upstairs hang out lounge. My husband ordered something with peanut sauce that he liked and I had the Greenhouse soup with a wonderful garlic taste. I recommend it!

The Dancing Dog Eatery & Juicery is my favorite restaurant in C-U. It is beautiful and comfortable and the food is sublime. This is vegan cuisine at a whole new culinary level - truly artful. They are open for brunch on Sundays now and I can't wait to try it.
